{"type":"message","id":"d138ee5d","parentId":"fa4712cd","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:51:36.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the problem clearly now. The cron is running fine - data is being fetched (175 sectors), but the write operation is failing with `Operation not permitted` on the `industries.csv` file. This is likely a SIP (System Integrity Protection) or file permission issue on macOS. The file is probably locked or owned by root.\n\nAlso the market pulse is showing data from April 7 (the pre-holiday session), not April 8. So the data hasn't actually been updated since before the holiday.\n\nLet me check the industries.csv file permissions.","thinkingSignature":"fb10501a0b9f7b16786586d0a6e817bcce14fcceaa100f3e57cae7d008a07703"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6bwy91r41jb6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/industries.csv 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6bwy91r41jb6_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/precheck_cron.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6527,"output":215,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26711,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775695889729,"responseId":"06262b11184111fdfb8a3dac78da843e"}}
