{"type":"message","id":"250e9f0b","parentId":"b13deb0d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:52:08.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now. The `data/` directory has permissions `drwx------` (700), which means only the owner (`ling`) can access it. But wait, there's also this:\n\n```\nlrwxrwxr-x   1 ling  staff       87 Mar 24 19:57 data -> /Volumes/A/openclaw-cold/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data\n```\n\nThe `data` directory is actually a **symbolic link** pointing to `/Volumes/A/openclaw-cold/...`. The actual data is on an external volume (`/Volumes/A/`). \n\nSo the cron job runs as `ling` and the symlink at `~/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/.../data` points to `/Volumes/A/openclaw-cold/workspace/.../data`. The symlink itself has `drwx------` permissions, which controls access through it. For symlinks, macOS typically ignores the symlink permissions and defers to the target directory's permissions, but the `Operation not permitted` error could be stemming from either the symlink itself being inaccessible or the target directory on the external volume having restrictive permissions.\n\nThe file timestamps are revealing—`industries.csv` was last modified on April 7, but the directory shows `Apr 8 00:32` for something, which suggests either the symlink target has different permissions or the `staff` group designation on macOS is playing a role here. Let me check what the actual permissions are on the target volume and whether cron is running with restricted group permissions.","thinkingSignature":"81121bc91e1f2fb35179ec2d28d63eb241fe7924905706000101ea9d2d3ab8fb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ii709q2k5cze_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Volumes/A/openclaw-cold/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/ 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"---\"; xattr -l /Volumes/A/openclaw-cold/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/data/industries.csv 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ii709q2k5cze_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if cron is actually running jobs\nps aux | grep -E \"cron|python3.*sync\" | grep -v grep | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8246,"output":465,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28680,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775695913989,"responseId":"06262b2b5f47c1068f193b1052fd8d99"}}
