{"type":"message","id":"580c7be5","parentId":"48aa54e2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:53:25.821Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait - the sector_sync log shows \"同步失败: [Errno 1] Operation not permitted\" but the data IS being fetched (175 sectors). The issue is that the script can't WRITE the file. But the data is fetched correctly.\n\nBut here's the key question: **is the data from today (April 8, the first trading day after Qingming) actually making it into the system?** \n\nLet me think about the full pipeline:\n1. `sync_sector_board_data.py` - fetches from Sina, tries to write to industries.csv → FAILS to write\n2. But `market_pulse.py` reads from `industries.csv`\n\n\n3. And `auto_run_premarket_precheck.py` reads from `industries.csv`\n\nSo if the write is failing, then `market_pulse.py` and the precheck are reading stale data from April 7. But when I checked `market_pulse.log`, it showed \"宽度87.4%[新鲜]\" which claims the data is fresh. Let me trace through what `market_pulse.py` actually does - it might be fetching the data differently than I thought, maybe not reading from the same CSV file.","thinkingSignature":"5ee73a2e35af59ed49d6f732e727e58f2f314adebe25729533a494b2b1a2d1b9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mlqo2hw7twzr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"industries\\|sector\\|数据\\|fresh\\|新鲜\" /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/market_pulse.py 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12100,"output":308,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32377,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775695997569,"responseId":"06262b7d22ee4a93d09c87a1ad0d6167"}}
