{"type":"message","id":"72a10800","parentId":"11952786","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:53:37.543Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - `market_pulse.py` reads from `sector_heatmap_summary.json`, not directly from `industries.csv`. And it checks the `generated_at` timestamp to determine freshness. The `[新鲜]` tag means the JSON file has a `generated_at` of today.\n\nBut wait - `sync_sector_board_data.py` writes BOTH `industries.csv` AND `sector_heatmap_summary.json`. If the CSV write fails, the JSON write might also fail. But the market_pulse says \"新鲜\" - so maybe the JSON IS being written successfully.\n\nLet me check the actual content of the `sector_heatmap_summary.json` to see when it was actually generated.","thinkingSignature":"58f78bafbfc9bf4558531e078d5448bca61a83255387e31146f10a3a04d2179a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s9lnqbltzfzf_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/sector_heatmap_summary.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('generated_at:', d.get('generated_at','N/A')); print('total_sectors:', d.get('total_sectors','N/A'))\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"file not found or invalid\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s9lnqbltzfzf_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system/research/reports/sector_heatmap_summary.json 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12706,"output":318,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32993,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775696005864,"responseId":"06262b8698e29dabef1cfcede6dc789d"}}
