{"type":"message","id":"3a108be1","parentId":"1b9aa5a2","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:55:19.667Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the `sector_heatmap_summary.json` has data from April 8 (the first trading day after Qingming). This is actually the right data. The `generated_at` is April 8 18:22 - after the market closed.\n\nBut wait - this was generated on April 8, and today is April 9. The cron job for `sync_sector_board_data.py` runs every 30 minutes during trading hours (9-11, 13-15). So it should have run today too. But the `sector_heatmap_summary.json` still shows April 8.\n\nThis means either:\n1. The cron job IS running today but the JSON write is failing for some reason\n\n\n2. The cron job is NOT running today\n\nLet me check the log file timestamp to figure out what's actually happening. The file shows `Apr 8 15:30` for the last entry, but if the cron job was running today at 10:00, I'd expect to see new log entries. Either the cron job didn't execute today, or it ran but failed to write to the log for some reason.\n\nActually, I should stop overthinking this. Let me just manually run the sync script right now to see if it works and what happens.","thinkingSignature":"13c62e8cac750b9b80c1d471c59eade69998de2fc7ac4486279b9df82d7d7aea"},{"type":"text","text":"\n好的，我看到真相了。让我先手动跑一次同步脚本，验证问题所在。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_akrjr49zov8n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && /usr/bin/python3 scripts/sync_sector_board_data.py 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18550,"output":350,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38869,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775696109885,"responseId":"06262bee7cea3c69af15037cd9e79b5a"}}
