{"type":"message","id":"4955e5d2","parentId":"2d47a470","timestamp":"2026-04-09T00:56:23.924Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`sector_heatmap_summary.json` now has `generated_at: 2026-04-09T08:55:43` - that's TODAY's data! The manual run just now (08:55) updated the JSON successfully.\n\nSo the immediate data freshness issue is FIXED (for now). The JSON has today's data.\n\nBut the `industries.csv` still gets written too (confirmed earlier). So both files are now updated.\n\nThe question is: **will the cron job on April 9 actually work, or will it fail again?** Based on the log, cron ran on April 8 at 15:30 (last log entry) but the JSON was updated at 18:22 - so it seems like something worked on April 8. \n\nLet me look at the cron entry to understand the timing. The job runs every 30 minutes during market hours, so it should have executed again at 09:00 today. I need to check the sector_sync.log to see if that 09:00 run actually succeeded or failed.","thinkingSignature":"d0f7b1ad8b4250b5e40cdff3e8fe3a6fd0cfc83255f59f4b4372195747ae364c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f6a8g250zydx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if today's 09:00 cron ran (check the log file modification time)\nls -la /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/logs/sector_sync.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21233,"output":279,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41481,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775696175901,"responseId":"06262c30ed88f0d0c874707f50d05007"}}
