{"type":"message","id":"9e6fb6dd","parentId":"eb75e41c","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:16:08.807Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. But wait - the ollama provider model `my-qwen` has ID `my-qwen` but the actual ollama model name is `my-qwen:latest`. And `gemma3:4b` doesn't seem to be in the ollama list (the list only showed `bge-m3:latest` and `carstenuhlig/omnicoder-9b:latest` and `deepseek-r1:7b` and `my-qwen:latest`).\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to update the model IDs in the provider to match the actual Ollama model names. This is important because OpenClaw will use these IDs to call the Ollama API.","thinkingSignature":"9330ace19d80debfeae323056d486e4400f28ab9ec197469e7d9e1333449f491"},{"type":"text","text":"注意到一个问题：`ollama provider` 里的 `my-qwen` 对应的实际模型是 `my-qwen:latest`，而 `gemma3:4b` 实际上不在 Ollama 里（Ollama 只装了 4 个）。来修正 provider 配置让 ID 和实际模型名一致：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0dg3hhs7zjpg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/Users/ling/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    d = json.load(f)\n\nproviders = d.get('models', {}).get('providers', {})\nollama = providers.get('ollama-local', {})\nmodels = ollama.get('models', [])\n\nfor m in models:\n    old_id = m['id']\n    # Fix known mismatches\n    if old_id == 'my-qwen':\n        m['id'] = 'my-qwen:latest'\n    elif old_id == 'gemma3:4b':\n        # Not actually installed, mark as unavailable or keep as-is\n        pass\n    print(f'  {old_id} → {m[\\\"id\\\"]}')\n\nprint(json.dumps(d, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\n\" > /tmp/openclaw_fix2.json && mv /tmp/openclaw_fix2.json ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json && echo \"OK\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":25957,"output":432,"cacheRead":19969,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46358,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697355637,"response