{"type":"message","id":"5741806b","parentId":"4290a571","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:18:06.423Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So llama.cpp is the source code. Let me check if there's a pre-built oMLX server or if I need to build it. Let me also check what models are available for oMLX and how to install them.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. oMLX typically refers to models that support Apple's MLX framework on Apple Silicon Macs. The llama.cpp directory is the source, but there might be a pre-built binary or a Docker setup.\n\nLet me check if there's a Docker setup or if oMLX models need to be downloaded separately.\n\nActually, the approach here might be:\n1. Delete Ollama models to free up disk space\n2. Download MLX-format models from HuggingFace or other sources\n\n\n3. Serve them via llama.cpp or a similar server\n\nI should clarify with the user what they want to accomplish - whether they're looking to serve models through oMLX, run Apple MLX format models directly, or just expand their local model library in general.","thinkingSignature":"5f0b1e9a1c2aa1fafdb28350ce791a1ce327c7d378fb22e0c39bebfc098cc701"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wbzhjmj8oadt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check disk space and which volume Ollama stores models on\ndf -h /usr/local/bin/ ~/.ollama/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check if there's an oMLX server binary somewhere\nfind /usr/local /opt/homebrew ~/.openclaw -maxdepth 4 -name \"server\" -o -name \"main\" -o -name \"llama-server\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".git\\|node_modules\" | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30072,"output":327,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50342,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697473854,"responseId":"06263142fa230717b3f58f7b8ef88d3b"}}
