{"type":"message","id":"b98c2057","parentId":"7f6631f4","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:18:19.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The llama.cpp source has a `tools/server` directory, but that's source code. The models are stored in `~/.ollama/` which is on the same volume as the data. We have 64GB free.\n\nNow let me understand what the user actually wants:\n- They want to delete Ollama models and use oMLX instead\n- oMLX in the context of this system seems to be a local model server running on port 8000\n- The models `Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct-4bit` and `Qwen2.5-1.5B-Instruct-4bit` were previously configured\n\n\n- oMLX isn't currently running on port 8000\n\nI should clarify whether oMLX refers to Apple's MLX framework for Apple Silicon, a specific model server they've set up, or something else entirely, and figure out how to get it running and install additional models through it.","thinkingSignature":"02b52acb9a4a6fba5279526c3e6ecabb89bd7b244b8c93adbbf274b092c35b45"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_okwvl3z77vgt_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's any oMLX setup documentation or config\ncat ~/.openclaw/credentials.env 2>/dev/null | grep -i omlx\nls ~/.openclaw/secrets/ 2>/dev/null\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport sys,json\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Look for any mention of omlx or port 8000\ntext = json.dumps(d)\nif '8000' in text:\n    print('Port 8000 found in config')\nif 'omlx' in text.lower():\n    print('oMLX found in config')\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30582,"output":348,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50873,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697487218,"responseId":"062631519c649571c3708da4b5796d25"}}
