{"type":"message","id":"5dcd20d9","parentId":"a16fac03","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:18:28.785Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about this differently. oMLX seems to refer to a local model server that was previously running on port 8000. Let me check what process was using port 8000, or if there's a startup script.\n\nActually, looking at the setup - the `omlx` provider in openclaw.json points to `http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1`. This is likely a llama.cpp server with MLX support built from the llama.cpp source in `~/.openclaw/llama.cpp/`.\n\nLet me check if there's a built binary or if I need to build one. Also, the models for oMLX are probably MLX-format models from HuggingFace.","thinkingSignature":"17e407cbe43a67be746f233dee29cabd9288d8e40d929e28ceaa8db9e94ce868"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5iowy706qug9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check what's on port 8000 or was supposed to be\nlsof -i :8000 2>/dev/null | head -5\n\n# Check if there's a built llama-server binary\nfind ~/.openclaw/llama.cpp -name \"llama-server\" -o -name \"server\" -type f 2>/dev/null | head -5\n\n# Check for any startup scripts\nls ~/.openclaw/scripts/ 2>/dev/null\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30975,"output":282,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51200,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697500037,"responseId":"0626315c6602315d1d88568437fb4aa9"}}
