{"type":"message","id":"6b85385f","parentId":"a87ffbd7","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:23:58.654Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me start the llama-server on port 8000. I'll need to figure out which models to load. Let me first check the available space for downloading GGUF models, then start the server and download models.Actually, let me first decide on the model variants. The original Ollama models were:- `my-qwen:latest` - This is Qwen3-9B or Qwen2.5-9B. I'll use `Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct-Q4_K_M.gguf` since 9B might be too large for GGUF- `deepseek-r1:7b` - DeepSeek R1 Distill Qwen 7B. \n\nFor the remaining models, I'm looking at the official Qwen GGUF variants from HuggingFace, DeepSeek-R1-Distill-Qwen-7B-Q4_K_M, and checking on OmniCoder's availability in GGUF format. I need to verify disk space before downloading, then start the server and pull the models.","thinkingSignature":"06d68710b372e1d131a9361616a875e3aeef2fb90baaf0d781dea9343f24fbce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_x820vdzyxmpc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"df -h /System/Volumes/Data 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40240,"output":248,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60431,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697829918,"responseId":"062632a6e067ee6ad1eaee63198a624e"}}
