{"type":"message","id":"3f765cf6","parentId":"146889df","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:24:41.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `llama-server` binary can't find the dynamic libraries because they are in `/tmp/llama-b8713/`. I need to either:\n1. Copy all the dylibs to a location the linker can find\n2. Set `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` when running\n3. Copy the binary to the same directory as the dylibs\n\nLet me set the `DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH` when launching.","thinkingSignature":"02d0524a923c40294861a098447a13dfac1f314f9c15353a501a9591ab2fa098"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_netugnfti9f0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# The dylibs are in /tmp/llama-b8713/ - need to set library path\n# Let's copy everything to ~/bin/llama/ for a self-contained install\nmkdir -p ~/bin/llama\ncp /tmp/llama-b8713/llama-server ~/bin/llama/\ncp /tmp/llama-b8713/lib*.dylib ~/bin/llama/\nchmod +x ~/bin/llama/llama-server\nls ~/bin/llama/ | head -10\n\n# Now start with correct library path\nexport DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=/Users/ling/bin/llama:$DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH\nnohup ~/bin/llama/llama-server \\\n  -ngl 99 \\\n  --host 127.0.0.1 \\\n  --port 8000 \\\n  > ~/workspace/logs/llama-server.log 2>&1 &\n\necho \"PID: $!\"\nsleep 5\ntail -5 ~/workspace/logs/llama-server.log 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41463,"output":336,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61742,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697871176,"responseId":"062632d069355bf09e2d03bedff9012c"}}
