{"type":"message","id":"8e708c2d","parentId":"d22d1792","timestamp":"2026-04-09T01:25:10.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server is running but no models are loaded (it runs in \"router mode\"). I need to manually load models using the API. The `llama-server` in this mode acts as a router and I'll need to use the API to pull/load models.\n\nActually, the way llama-server works is that you specify models via command line or you use the `/v1/models` endpoint which lists available models - but the models themselves need to be downloaded separately and then loaded.\n\nFor llama.cpp with GGUF models, you typically:\n1. Download GGUF files from HuggingFace\n2. Specify them with `-m model.gguf` when starting the server","thinkingSignature":"0683d96ea6aa324c26790bfecc4e43f958530ec846b32e1234da9cd73f913ada"},{"type":"text","text":"Server 跑起来了（路由模式，无模型加载）。接下来下载 GGUF 模型。先确认可用模型列表：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c7kox0tyyx4n_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Verify server is up\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/models 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('Models:', [m['id'] for m in d.get('data',[])])\" 2>/dev/null\n\n# Check how much space we need for models\n# Qwen2.5-7B-Q4_K_M ~ 4.5GB, DeepSeek-R1-Distill-Qwen-7B-Q4_K_M ~ 4.5GB\necho \"---\"\necho \"Disk space: $(df -h /System/Volumes/Data | tail -1 | awk '{print $4}') free\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42295,"output":338,"cacheRead":19943,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775697897848,"responseId":"062632ea3dab4a4b3017bfd103367be1"}}
