{"type":"message","id":"22ad8aee","parentId":"ccf6fa7d","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:00:41.878Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The download process was terminated. Let me try a simpler approach - use curl/wget directly to download from HuggingFace, or check if there's an issue with the network/huggingface hub.\n\nActually, given the complications with downloading large models and the time it's taking, I should give the user a status update and ask for their preference on next steps.\n\nLet me check what we have so far:\n1. ✅ Ollama models deleted\n2. ✅ llama-server downloaded and running on port 8000\n3. ❌ Model downloads failing/taking too long\n\nOptions:\n1. Try smaller models first\n2. Wait for Qwen2.5-7B to finish downloading\n3. Try a different model source\n","thinkingSignature":"1f6e52b26a76485fd46267992cad1c4bd6f9ea600682ace8cf66b1006b46bee0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v6j6fafldi16_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check current state\necho \"=== Ollama ===\"\nollama list 2>/dev/null || echo \"Ollama no models\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== llama-server (port 8000) ===\"\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1/models 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('Models:', [m['id'] for m in d.get('data',[])])\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"Server not responding\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Check if any GGUF files downloaded ===\"\nls -la /Users/ling/Models/gguf/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No GGUF folder yet\"\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Disk space ===\"\ndf -h /System/Volumes/Data 2>/dev/null | tail -1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":184,"output":355,"cacheRead":67200,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67739,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775700017759,"responseId":"06263b3a42cce75707c7a1cea9bd9194"}}
