{"type":"message","id":"9fa6ed5a","parentId":"00145a54","timestamp":"2026-04-09T07:16:47.567Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The codex config already has `gmn` as a provider and `gpt-5.4` is configured in the `auto-max` profile. But the `base_url` is `https://gmncode.cn` which might not be the right endpoint for the `responses` API. Let me check what the user actually needs.\n\nLooking at the user's requested config:\n```\nmodel_provider = \"OpenAI\"\nmodel = \"gpt-5.4\"\nreview_model = \"gpt-5.4\"\nmodel_reasoning_effort = \"xhigh\"\ndisable_response_storage = true\nnetwork_access = \"enabled\"\n\n\n```\n\nI see they want `model_provider = \"OpenAI\"` but the current config uses `\"gmn\"` for the provider name. The user seems to want to use the `OpenAI` provider name while pointing to the gmncode.cn endpoint. I need to check if Codex CLI supports multiple provider configurations or if they just want to rename the existing gmn provider to OpenAI.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the config they provided, they're specifying `base_url = \"https://gmncode.cn\"` and `wire_api = \"responses\"` which suggests they want the gmn endpoint but under an \"OpenAI\" provider label. I should update the `[model_providers.OpenAI]` section to use the correct base URL and wire_api settings, and make sure the model and reasoning effort are properly configured.\n\n```\n\ntoml\n[model_providers.OpenAI]\nname = \"OpenAI\"\nbase_url = \"https://gmncode.cn\"\nwire_api = \"responses\"\nrequires_openai_auth = true\n```\n\nThe `model_context_window = 1000000` and `model_auto_compact_token_limit = 900000` might be workspace-specific settings rather than global config. I need to clarify with the user whether these should be set globally or per-project, since the context window is unusually large at 1M tokens and the auto-compact threshold at 900K suggests they're working with very large contexts. The user's config shows `model_provider = \"OpenAI\"` but the current setup uses `\"gmn\"` instead, so I should clarify whether they want me to rename the provider or update the existing one. Looking at the rest of their config with the extreme context window of 1M tokens and auto-compact at 900K, these are atypical Codex settings that suggest they might be copying from documentation or a different system entirely. I should ask for clarification on what they're actually trying to accomplish with these specific parameter values. These settings look like they'd be in a workspace-specific configuration rather than the global config. Let me consolidate what the user actually needs: updating the gmn provider's base_url and wire_api settings, switching the model to gpt-5.4, setting reasoning effort to xhigh, and making sure the API key is properly configured. I'm also wondering if `requires_openai_auth = true` is necessary given the gmn provider already has its own authentication mechanism. The gpt-5.4 model with 1M context window looks like it might be an unpublished OpenAI model, so I should clarify whether that's the right choice for what they're trying to do. I need to finish that thought about the Codex CLI config file—it uses TOML format, so the user's configuration needs to match that. Let me write out the complete updated config with all the changes they've requested. I'm checking the Codex CLI configuration schema to understand what `wire_api` controls and how the `responses` API works. It looks like Codex supports different API types including completions, chat, and responses, so setting `wire_api = \"responses\"` should be valid. Let me finalize the config with the correct settings.","thinkingSignature":"a2fa6f94023d2178b0a0f7f4840d30db846960f80f3f5e2729016bc48be91d9a"},{"type":"text","text":"Codex 已经配置了 `gmn` provider 和 `gpt-5.4`。我来更新成你要的配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5jgrigkyb5bm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat > ~/.codex/config.toml << 'EOF'\nmodel = \"gpt-5.4\"\nmodel_reasoning_